<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,890,1347]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1286,1311]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
The pygofer, its ventral process and the structure of the aedeagus place this species in 
<emphasis box="[1322,1403,1286,1311]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Apphia</emphasis>
. It closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[356,443,1322,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flava" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[356,443,1322,1347]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[450,540,1322,1347]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[450,540,1322,1347]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but lacks the basal quadrate lobes of the aedeagal shaft (see below).
</paragraph>
